e don’t add metadata to test helpers unless it's required.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class and method access**\\n\\nI’m thinking about public inner non-static classes and filtering static ones. Using `getPublicStaticClassNames` helps with that, and for `getClass`, it's all about finding by the simple name. \\n\\nMeanwhile, `getPublicFieldNames` lets me access public fields through `obj.getClass().getFields()`, and it's crucial to include metadata. I see `getPublicStaticFieldNames` operates similarly for static fields, while `getPublicMethodNames` works with `getMethods` to include methods too. There’s a lot to keep track of!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1q5FDoGcSQTYksvUtqtMjNd8|fc_0a385e3523b47e330169f11570869c81959358c5afda1945ae", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"allPublicClasses|allDeclaredClasses|queryAll|queried\" . | head -100", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3500, "output": 1351, "cacheRead": 45056, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49907, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777407321242, "responseId": "resp_0a385e3523b47e330169f11559e84c8195b928c4f0be071e28"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_1q5FDoGcSQTYksvUtqtMjNd8|fc_0a385e3523b47e330169f11570869c81959358c5afda1945ae", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "./tests/src/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/jakarta.xml.bind/jakarta.xml.bind-api/3.0.1/reflect-config.json:195:    \"queryAllDeclaredMethods\": true\n./tests/src/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/jakarta.xml.bind/jakarta.xml.bind-api/3.0.1/reflect-config.json:247:    \"queryAllPublicConstructors\": true,\n./tests/src/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/jakarta.xml.bind/jakart